.TH "fsverity_verify_signature" 9 "fsverity_verify_signature" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsverity_verify_signature \- check a verity file's signature
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fsverity_verify_signature
.BI "(const struct fsverity_info *vi "  ","
.BI "const u8 *signature "  ","
.BI "size_t sig_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vi" 12
the file's fsverity_info
.IP "signature" 12
the file's built-in signature
.IP "sig_size" 12
size of signature in bytes, or 0 if no signature
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the file includes a signature of its fs-verity file digest, verify it
against the certificates in the fs-verity keyring.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success (signature valid or not required); -errno on failure
